    "text": "East 4th Street, north side, west from (No. 35-31, garage), a point midway between the Bowery and Lafayette Street, and to the latter (left). The 3\u00bd-story structure with dormer windows is the \"Old Merchants House\" built by Seabury Tredwell in 1836 and occupied by him and his spinster daughters until 1930. It is now a historical museum, under the auspices of the Historic Landmark Society. For a full account see the New York Times, Sunday May 3, 1936.\n\nDecember 9, 1937.\n\nGeorge D. Chinn.\n",
